a 70% increase versus the prior year</font></div><div style="margin-top:2pt;text-indent:22.5pt"><font><br></font></div><div style="margin-top:2pt;text-indent:22.5pt"><font style="color:#000000;font-family:'Times New Roman',sans-serif;font-size:10pt;font-weight:400;line-height:120%">CHICAGO, IL - McDonald's Corporation today announced results for the second quarter ended June&#160;30, 2021.</font></div><div style="margin-top:4.5pt;text-indent:28pt"><font><br></font></div><div style="margin-top:4.5pt;text-indent:28pt"><font style="color:#000000;font-family:'Times New Roman',sans-serif;font-size:10pt;font-weight:400;line-height:112%">&#8220;Our performance is a continued demonstration of the broad-based strength and resiliency of our business as global comp sales in the second quarter increased nearly 7% over 2019.  For 65 years, we&#8217;ve created iconic experiences for billions of people around the world. Along the way, we&#8217;ve always focused on following our customers&#8217; needs, finding the most convenient and engaging ways for them to enjoy McDonald&#8217;s. It&#8217;s clear that our next chapter will be driven by our leadership in digital,&#8221; said McDonald&#8217;s President and Chief Executive Officer Chris Kempczinski. &#8220;As we build on our momentum and embed our digital capabilities through the customer experience, I&#8217;m thrilled that Manu Steijaert will be taking on the newly created role of Chief Customer Officer. His team will deliver the seamless omnichannel experience that our customers want and McDonald&#8217;s can provide.&#8221;</font></div><div style="margin-top:2pt;text-indent:22.5pt"><font><br></font></div><div style="margin-top:2pt;text-indent:22.5pt"><font style="color:#000000;font-family:'Times New style="margin-top:9pt;padding-left:22.5pt;text-indent:36pt"><font style="color:#000000;font-family:'Times New Roman',sans-serif;font-size:10pt;font-weight:400;line-height:112%">COVID-19 resurgences throughout the quarter and six months have resulted in instances of government restrictions on restaurant operating hours, limited dine-in capacity and, in some cases, dining room closures. The Company has continued to follow the guidance of expert health authorities to apply the appropriate precautionary measures to protect the health and safety of our people and our customers and expects some operating restrictions in various markets so long as the COVID-19 pandemic continues.</font></div><div style="margin-top:4.5pt;padding-left:22.5pt;text-indent:-4.5pt"><font><br></font></div><div style="padding-left:22.5pt;text-indent:-22.5pt"><font style="color:#000000;font-family:'Times New Roman',sans-serif;font-size:10pt;font-weight:400;line-height:112%">&#8226;</font><font style="color:#000000;font-family:'Times New Roman',sans-serif;font-size:10pt;font-weight:700;line-height:112%;padding-left:19pt">Comparable Sales&#58;</font><font style="color:#000000;font-family:'Times New Roman',sans-serif;font-size:10pt;font-weight:400;line-height:112%"> Quarterly comparable sales and guest counts were positive across all segments. Comparable sales were impacted in both periods (to a greater extent in 2020) by COVID-19.</font></div><div style="text-indent:-4.5pt"><font><br></font></div><div style="padding-left:58.5pt;text-indent:-22.5pt"><font style="color:#000000;font-family:'Times New Roman',sans-serif;font-size:10pt;font-weight:400;line-height:112%">&#8226;</font><font style="color:#000000;font-family:'Times New Roman',sans-serif;font-size:10pt;font-weight:700;line-height:112%;padding-left:19pt">U.S.&#58; </font><font style="color:#000000;font-family:'Times New Roman',sans-serif;font-size:10pt;font-weight:400;line-height:112%">Comparable sales results benefited from strong average check growth driven by larger order size and menu price increases. The Crispy Chicken Sandwich and BTS Famous Order promotion, as well as growth in delivery and digital platforms, contributed to the comparable sales growth. Comparable sales increased 14.9% on a 2-year basis, reflecting continued momentum.</font></div><div style="padding-left:22.5pt;text-indent:-4.5pt"><font><br></font></div><div style="padding-left:58.5pt;text-indent:-22.5pt"><font style="color:#000000;font-family:'Arial',sans-serif;font-size:10pt;font-weight:400;line-height:112%">&#8226;</font><font style="color:#000000;font-family:'Times New Roman',sans-serif;font-size:10pt;font-weight:700;line-height:112%;padding-left:19pt">International Operated Markets&#58;</font><font style="color:#000000;font-family:'Times New Roman',sans-serif;font-size:10pt;font-weight:400;line-height:112%"> Results reflected strong positive comparable sales in the U.K. and France as well as positive comparable sales across the entire segment due to significantly fewer restaurant closures and the easing of COVID-19 restrictions. Comparable sales increased 2.6% on a 2-year basis, reflecting positive 2-year comparable sales in the U.K., Australia and Canada and negative 2-year comparable sales in France and Germany.</font></div><div style="padding-left:22.5pt;text-indent:-4.5pt"><font><br></font></div><div style="padding-left:58.5pt;text-indent:-22.5pt"><font style="color:#000000;font-family:'Arial',sans-serif;font-size:10pt;font-weight:400;line-height:112%">&#8226;</font><font style="color:#000000;font-family:'Times New Roman',sans-serif;font-size:10pt;font-weight:700;line-height:112%;padding-left:19pt">International Developmental Licensed Markets&#58;</font><font style="color:#000000;font-family:'Times New Roman',sans-serif;font-size:10pt;font-weight:400;line-height:112%"> The strong quarterly comparable sales were primarily driven by Brazil, Japan and China, along with positive comparable sales across all regions. Comparable sales increased 0.3% on a 2-year basis. </font></div><div style="margin-top:2.5pt"><font><br></font></div><div><font style="color:#000000;font-family:'Times New style="margin-top:6pt"><font style="color:#000000;font-family:'Times New Roman',sans-serif;font-size:10pt;font-weight:400;line-height:120%">n&#47;m Not meaningful</font></div><div style="margin-top:6pt;text-indent:22.5pt"><font><br></font></div><div style="margin-top:9pt"><font><br></font></div><div style="margin-top:9pt"><font><br></font></div><div style="margin-top:9pt"><font><br></font></div><div style="height:45pt;position:relative;width:100%"><div style="bottom:0;position:absolute;width:100%"><div style="text-align:center"><font style="color:#000000;font-family:'Times New Roman',sans-serif;font-size:10pt;font-weight:400;line-height:120%">3</font></div></div></div><hr style="page-break-after:always"><div style="min-height:45pt;width:100%"><div><font><br></font></div></div><div style="margin-top:6pt"><font style="color:#000000;font-family:'Times New Roman',sans-serif;font-size:10pt;font-weight:700;line-height:120%">THE FOLLOWING DEFINITIONS APPLY TO THESE TERMS AS USED THROUGHOUT THIS RELEASE</font></div><div style="margin-top:4pt;text-indent:22.5pt"><font style="color:#000000;font-family:'Times New Roman',sans-serif;font-size:10pt;font-weight:400;line-height:120%">Constant currency results exclude the effects of foreign currency translation and are calculated by translating current year results at prior year average exchange rates. Management reviews and analyzes business results excluding the effect of foreign currency translation, impairment and other strategic charges and gains, as well as material regulatory and other income tax impacts, and bases incentive compensation plans on these results because the Company believes this better represents underlying business trends.</font></div><div style="margin-top:4.5pt;text-indent:22.5pt"><font style="color:#000000;font-family:'Times New Roman',sans-serif;font-size:10pt;font-weight:400;line-height:120%">Comparable sales are compared to the same period in the prior year and represent sales at all restaurants, whether operated by the Company or by franchisees, in operation at least thirteen months including those temporarily closed. Some of the reasons restaurants may be temporarily closed include reimaging or remodeling, rebuilding, road construction and natural disasters (including restaurants temporarily closed due to COVID-19). Comparable sales exclude the impact of currency translation and the sales of any market considered hyper-inflationary (generally identified as those markets whose cumulative inflation rate over a three-year period exceeds 100%), which management believes more accurately reflects the underlying business trends. Comparable sales are driven by changes in guest counts and average check, the latter of which is affected by changes in pricing and product mix. </font></div><div style="margin-top:4pt;text-indent:22.5pt"><font style="color:#000000;font-family:'Times New Roman',sans-serif;font-size:10pt;font-weight:400;line-height:120%">Comparable guest counts represent the number of transactions at all restaurants, whether operated by the Company or by franchisees, in operation at least thirteen months including those temporarily closed. </font></div><div style="margin-top:4pt;text-indent:22.5pt"><font style="color:#000000;font-family:'Times New Roman',sans-serif;font-size:10pt;font-weight:400;line-height:120%">Systemwide sales include sales at all restaurants, whether operated by the Company or by franchisees. While franchised sales are not recorded as revenues by the Company, management believes the information is important in understanding the Company's financial performance because these sales are the basis on which the Company calculates and records franchised revenues and are indicative of the financial health of the franchisee base. The Company's revenues consist of sales by Company-operated restaurants and fees from franchised restaurants operated by conventional franchisees, developmental licensees and affiliates. Changes in Systemwide sales are primarily driven by comparable sales and net restaurant unit expansion. </font></div><div style="margin-top:4pt;text-indent:22.5pt"><font style="color:#000000;font-family:'Times New Roman',sans-serif;font-size:10pt;font-weight:400;line-height:120%">Free cash flow, defined as cash provided by operations less capital expenditures, and free cash flow conversion rate, defined as free cash flow divided by net income (excluding the effect of impairment and other strategic charges and gains, as well as material regulatory and other income tax impacts), are measures reviewed by management in order to evaluate the Company&#8217;s ability to convert net profits into cash resources, after reinvesting in the core business, that can be used to pursue opportunities to enhance shareholder value. </font></div><div style="margin-top:6pt"><font style="color:#000000;font-family:'Times New Roman',sans-serif;font-size:10pt;font-weight:700;line-height:120%">RELATED COMMUNICATIONS </font></div><div style="margin-top:4pt;text-indent:22.5pt"><font style="color:#000000;font-family:'Times New Roman',sans-serif;font-size:10pt;font-weight:400;line-height:120%">This press release should be read in conjunction with Exhibit </font><font style="color:#0000ff;font-family:'Times New Roman',sans-serif;font-size:10pt;font-weight:400;line-height:120%;text-decoration:underline"><a href="exhibit992-6302021.htm" style="color:#0000ff;font-family:'Times New Roman',sans-serif;font-size:10pt;font-weight:400;line-height:120%"> to the Company's Form 8-K filing for supplemental information related to the Company's results for the quarter and six months ended June&#160;30, 2021.</font></div><div style="margin-top:4pt;text-indent:22.5pt"><font style="color:#000000;font-family:'Times New Roman',sans-serif;font-size:10pt;font-weight:400;line-height:120%">McDonald&#8217;s Corporation will broadcast its investor earnings conference call live over the Internet at 7&#58;30 a.m. (Central Time) on July&#160;28, 2021. A link to the live webcast will be available at </font><font style="color:#0563c1;font-family:'Times New Roman',sans-serif;font-size:10pt;font-weight:400;line-height:120%;text-decoration:underline">www.investor.mcdonalds.com</font><font style="color:#000000;font-family:'Times New Roman',sans-serif;font-size:10pt;font-weight:400;line-height:120%">. There will also be an archived webcast available for a limited time thereafter.</font></div><div style="margin-top:6pt"><font style="color:#000000;font-family:'Times New Roman',sans-serif;font-size:10pt;font-weight:700;line-height:120%">UPCOMING COMMUNICATIONS </font></div><div style="margin-top:5pt;text-indent:22.5pt"><font style="color:#000000;font-family:'Times New Roman',sans-serif;font-size:10pt;font-weight:400;line-height:120%">For important news and information regarding McDonald's, including the timing of future investor conferences and earnings calls, visit the Investor Relations section of the Company's Internet home page at </font><font style="color:#0563c1;font-family:'Times New Roman',sans-serif;font-size:10pt;font-weight:400;line-height:120%;text-decoration:underline">www.investor.mcdonalds.com</font><font style="color:#000000;font-family:'Times New Roman',sans-serif;font-size:10pt;font-weight:400;line-height:120%">. McDonald's uses this website as a primary channel for disclosing key information to its investors, some of which may contain material and previously non-public information.</font></div><div style="margin-top:5pt"><font style="color:#000000;font-family:'Times New Roman',sans-serif;font-size:10pt;font-weight:700;line-height:120%">ABOUT McDONALD&#8217;S</font></div><div style="margin-top:5pt;text-indent:22.5pt"><font style="color:#000000;font-family:'Times New Roman',sans-serif;font-size:10pt;font-weight:400;line-height:120%">McDonald&#8217;s is the world&#8217;s leading global foodservice retailer with over 39,000 locations in over 100 countries. Approximately 93% of McDonald&#8217;s restaurants worldwide are owned and operated by independent local business owners.</font></div><div style="margin-top:6pt"><font style="color:#000000;font-family:'Times New Roman',sans-serif;font-size:10pt;font-weight:700;line-height:120%">FORWARD-LOOKING STATEMENTS </font></div><div style="margin-top:5pt;text-indent:22.5pt"><font style="color:#000000;font-family:'Times New Roman',sans-serif;font-size:10pt;font-weight:400;line-height:120%">This release contains certain forward-looking statements, which reflect management's expectations regarding future events and operating performance and speak only as of the date hereof. New Roman',sans-serif;font-size:10pt;font-weight:400;line-height:120%">The purpose of this exhibit is to provide additional information related to the results of McDonald's Corporation (the &#8220;Company&#8221;) for the quarter and six months ended June&#160;30, 2021. This exhibit should be read in conjunction with Exhibit </font><font style="color:#0000ff;font-family:'Times New Roman',sans-serif;font-size:10pt;font-weight:400;line-height:120%;text-decoration:underline"><a href="exhibit991-6302021.htm" style="color:#0000ff;font-family:'Times New Roman',sans-serif;font-size:10pt;font-weight:400;line-height:120%;text-decoration:underline">99.1</a></font><font style="color:#000000;font-family:'Times New Roman',sans-serif;font-size:10pt;font-weight:400;line-height:120%">.</font></div><div style="margin-top:4.5pt;text-indent:22.5pt"><font style="color:#000000;font-family:'Times New Roman',sans-serif;font-size:10pt;font-weight:400;line-height:112%">Management reviews and analyzes business results excluding the effect of foreign currency translation, impairment and other strategic charges and gains, as well as material regulatory and other income tax impacts, and bases incentive compensation plans on these results because the Company believes this better represents underlying business trends.</font></div><div id="i9f69d7e15d424fb0868db396c4337e5a_7"></div><div><font><br></font></div><div><font style="color:#000000;font-family:'Times New Roman',sans-serif;font-size:10pt;font-weight:700;line-height:120%">Impact of Foreign Currency Translation </font></div><div style="margin-top:4.5pt;text-indent:22.5pt"><font style="color:#000000;font-family:'Times New Roman',sans-serif;font-size:10pt;font-weight:400;line-height:120%">While changes in foreign currency exchange rates affect reported results, McDonald's mitigates exposures, where practical, by purchasing goods and services in local currencies, financing in local currencies and hedging certain foreign-denominated cash flows. Results excluding the effect of foreign currency translation (referred to as constant currency) are calculated by translating current year results at prior year average exchange rates. style="margin-top:6pt"><font style="color:#000000;font-family:'Times New Roman',sans-serif;font-size:10pt;font-weight:400;line-height:120%">n&#47;m Not meaningful</font></div><div style="margin-top:6pt;text-indent:22.5pt"><font style="color:#000000;font-family:'Times New Roman',sans-serif;font-size:10pt;font-weight:400;line-height:120%">Excluding the strategic gains and income tax benefits, net income was $1,784.8 million and diluted earnings per share was $2.37 for the quarter, and net income was $3,223.1 million and diluted earnings per share was $4.29 for the six months.</font></div><div style="margin-top:6pt;text-indent:22.5pt"><font style="color:#000000;font-family:'Times New Roman',sans-serif;font-size:10pt;font-weight:400;line-height:120%">In the second quarter, the Company paid a quarterly dividend of $1.29 per share, or $963.3 million, bringing total dividends paid for the six months to $1.9 billion.</font></div><div style="margin-top:4.5pt;text-indent:22.5pt"><font><br></font></div><div style="margin-top:4.5pt"><font><br></font></div><div style="height:45pt;position:relative;width:100%"><div style="bottom:0;position:absolute;width:100%"><div style="text-align:center"><font style="color:#000000;font-family:'Times New Roman',sans-serif;font-size:10pt;font-weight:400;line-height:120%">2</font></div></div></div><div id="i9f69d7e15d424fb0868db396c4337e5a_13"></div><hr style="page-break-after:always"><div style="min-height:45pt;width:100%"><div><font><br></font></div></div><div><font style="color:#000000;font-family:'Times New Roman',sans-serif;font-size:10pt;font-weight:700;line-height:120%">Revenues </font></div><div style="margin-top:4.5pt;text-indent:22.5pt"><font style="color:#000000;font-family:'Times New Roman',sans-serif;font-size:10pt;font-weight:400;line-height:120%">The Company's revenues consist of sales by Company-operated restaurants and fees from restaurants operated by franchisees, developmental licensees and affiliates. Revenues from conventional franchised restaurants include rent and royalties based on a percent of sales with minimum rent payments, and initial fees. Revenues from restaurants licensed to developmental licensees and affiliates include a royalty based on a percent of sales, and generally include initial fees. The Company&#8217;s Other revenues are comprised of fees paid by franchisees to recover a portion of costs incurred by the Company for various technology platforms, revenues from brand licensing arrangements to market and sell consumer packaged goods using the McDonald&#8217;s brand, and third party revenues for the Dynamic Yield business.</font></div><div style="margin-top:4.5pt;text-indent:22.5pt"><font style="color:#000000;font-family:'Times New Roman',sans-serif;font-size:10pt;font-weight:400;line-height:120%">Franchised restaurants represented 93% of McDonald's restaurants worldwide at June&#160;30, 2021. The Company's heavily franchised business model is designed to generate stable and predictable revenue, which is largely a function of franchisee sales, and resulting cash flow streams. </font></div><div style="margin-top:4.5pt;text-indent:22.5pt"><font style="color:#000000;font-family:'Times New Roman',sans-serif;font-size:10pt;font-weight:400;line-height:120%">COVID-19 resurgences throughout the quarter and six months have resulted in instances of government restrictions on restaurant operating hours, limited dine-in capacity and, in some cases, dining room closures. The Company has continued to follow the guidance of expert health authorities to apply the appropriate precautionary measures to protect the health and safety of our people and our customers and expects some operating restrictions in various markets so long as the COVID-19 pandemic continues.</font></div><div style="margin-top:10pt"><font style="color:#000000;font-family:'Times New Roman',sans-serif;font-size:10pt;font-weight:400;line-height:120%">REVENUES </font></div><div style="margin-bottom:5pt"><font style="color:#000000;font-family:'Times New Roman',sans-serif;font-size:10pt;font-weight:400;line-height:100%">%</font></td></tr><tr style="height:6pt"><td colspan="3" style="padding:0 1pt"></td><td colspan="3" style="padding:0 1pt"></td><td colspan="3" style="padding:0 1pt"></td><td colspan="3" style="padding:0 1pt"></td><td colspan="3" style="padding:0 1pt"></td><td colspan="3" style="padding:0 1pt"></td></tr><tr style="height:6pt"><td colspan="3" style="border-top:1pt solid #000000;padding:0 1pt"></td><td colspan="3" style="border-top:1pt solid #000000;padding:0 1pt"></td><td colspan="3" style="border-top:1pt solid style="border-top:1pt solid #000000;padding:0 1pt"></td></tr></table></div><div style="margin-top:4.5pt;padding-left:36pt;text-indent:-18pt"><font style="color:#000000;font-family:'Times New Roman',sans-serif;font-size:10pt;font-weight:400;line-height:120%">&#8226;</font><font style="color:#000000;font-family:'Times New Roman',sans-serif;font-size:10pt;font-weight:400;line-height:120%;padding-left:14.5pt">Total Company-operated sales and franchised revenues increased 57% (50% in constant currencies) for the quarter and 30% (25% in constant currencies) for the six months. Both periods reflected strong sales performance in the International Operated Markets segment driven by the U.K., France and Russia, as well as in the U.S., as government imposed COVID-19 restrictions were gradually lifted. Both periods also reflected strong sales performance in the International Developmental Licensed Markets driven by China.</font></div><div style="margin-top:4.5pt;padding-left:22.5pt"><font><br></font></div><div id="i9f69d7e15d424fb0868db396c4337e5a_19"></div><div style="margin-top:3pt"><font style="color:#000000;font-family:'Times New Roman',sans-serif;font-size:10pt;font-weight:700;line-height:120%">Comparable Sales</font></div><div style="margin-top:4.5pt;text-indent:22.5pt"><font style="color:#000000;font-family:'Times New Roman',sans-serif;font-size:10pt;font-weight:400;line-height:120%">Comparable sales is a key performance indicator used within the retail industry and is reviewed by management to assess business trends. Comparable sales exclude the impact of currency translation and sales from hyper-inflationary markets. Increases or decreases in comparable sales represent the percent change in constant currency sales from the same period in the prior year for all restaurants, whether operated by the Company or by franchisees, in operation at least thirteen months, including those temporarily closed (including restaurants temporarily closed due to COVID-19). Comparable sales are driven by changes in guest counts and average check, the latter of which is affected by changes in pricing and product mix. </font></div><div style="color:#000000;font-family:'Times New Roman',sans-serif;font-size:10pt;font-weight:400;line-height:120%">The following tables present Systemwide sales growth rates and franchised sales. Systemwide sales include sales at all restaurants, whether operated by the Company or by franchisees. While franchised sales are not recorded as revenues by the Company, management believes the information is important in understanding the Company's financial performance because these sales are the basis on which the Company calculates and records franchised revenues and are indicative of the financial health of the franchisee base. Changes in Systemwide sales are primarily driven by comparable sales and net restaurant unit expansion.</font></div><div style="margin-top:8pt"><font style="color:#000000;font-family:'Times New style="height:45pt;position:relative;width:100%"><div style="bottom:0;position:absolute;width:100%"><div style="text-align:center"><font style="color:#000000;font-family:'Times New Roman',sans-serif;font-size:10pt;font-weight:400;line-height:120%">5</font></div></div></div><div id="i9f69d7e15d424fb0868db396c4337e5a_25"></div><hr style="page-break-after:always"><div style="min-height:45pt;width:100%"><div><font><br></font></div></div><div><font style="color:#000000;font-family:'Times New Roman',sans-serif;font-size:10pt;font-weight:700;line-height:120%">Restaurant Margins </font></div><div><font><br></font></div><div style="text-indent:36pt"><font style="color:#000000;font-family:'Times New Roman',sans-serif;font-size:10pt;font-weight:400;line-height:120%">Franchised restaurant margins are measured as revenues from franchised restaurants less franchised restaurant occupancy costs. Franchised revenues include rent and royalties based on a percent of sales, and initial fees. Franchised restaurant occupancy costs include lease expense and depreciation, as the Company generally owns or secures a long-term lease on the land and building for the restaurant location.</font></div><div><font><br></font></div><div style="text-indent:36pt"><font style="color:#000000;font-family:'Times New Roman',sans-serif;font-size:10pt;font-weight:400;line-height:120%">Company-operated restaurant margins are measured as sales from Company-operated restaurants less costs for food &#38; paper, payroll &#38; employee benefits and occupancy &#38; other operating expenses necessary to run an individual restaurant. Company-operated margins exclude costs that are not allocated to individual restaurants, primarily payroll &#38; employee benefit costs of non-restaurant support staff, which are included in selling, general and administrative expenses.</font></div><div><font><br></font></div><div style="margin-top:4.5pt"><font style="color:#000000;font-family:'Times New Roman',sans-serif;font-size:10pt;font-weight:400;line-height:120%">RESTAURANT MARGINS </font></div><div><font style="color:#000000;font-family:'Times New Roman',sans-serif;font-size:10pt;font-weight:400;line-height:120%">Dollars in millions </font><font style="color:#000000;font-family:'Times New Roman',sans-serif;font-size:4pt;font-weight:400;line-height:120%">&#160;</font></div><div style="margin-top:5pt;text-align:center"><table style="border-collapse:collapse;display:inline-table;margin-bottom:5pt;vertical-align:text-bottom;width:100.000%"><tr><td style="width:1.0%"></td><td style="width:64.491%"></td><td Franchised margins represented over 85% of restaurant margin dollars for the quarter and six months.</font></div><div style="margin-top:4.5pt;padding-left:22.5pt;text-indent:-22.5pt"><font style="color:#000000;font-family:'Times New Roman',sans-serif;font-size:10pt;font-weight:400;line-height:120%">&#8226;</font><font style="color:#000000;font-family:'Times New Roman',sans-serif;font-size:10pt;font-weight:400;line-height:120%;padding-left:19pt">U.S. franchised margins for both periods reflected higher depreciation costs related to investments in restaurant modernization and the comparison to prior year support provided for marketing to accelerate recovery and drive growth.</font></div><div style="height:45pt;position:relative;width:100%"><div style="bottom:0;position:absolute;width:100%"><div style="text-align:center"><font style="color:#000000;font-family:'Times New Roman',sans-serif;font-size:10pt;font-weight:400;line-height:120%">6</font></div></div></div><hr style="page-break-after:always"><div style="min-height:45pt;width:100%"><div><font><br></font></div></div><div style="margin-top:4.5pt;padding-left:22.5pt;text-indent:-22.5pt"><font style="color:#000000;font-family:'Times New Roman',sans-serif;font-size:10pt;font-weight:400;line-height:120%">&#8226;</font><font style="color:#000000;font-family:'Times New Roman',sans-serif;font-size:10pt;font-weight:400;line-height:120%;padding-left:19pt">Total restaurant margins included $379.0 million and $755.6 million of depreciation and amortization expense for the quarter and six months, respectively.</font></div><div style="margin-top:4.5pt;text-indent:-4.5pt"><font><br></font></div><div id="i9f69d7e15d424fb0868db396c4337e5a_31"></div><div><font style="color:#000000;font-family:'Times New Roman',sans-serif;font-size:10pt;font-weight:700;line-height:120%">Selling, General &#38; Prior year results for both periods also reflected $31 million of payments to distribution centers for obsolete inventory to support franchisee liquidity.</font></div><div style="margin-top:4.5pt;padding-left:22.5pt;text-indent:-22.5pt"><font style="color:#000000;font-family:'Times New Roman',sans-serif;font-size:10pt;font-weight:400;line-height:120%">&#8226;</font><font style="color:#000000;font-family:'Times New Roman',sans-serif;font-size:10pt;font-weight:400;line-height:120%;padding-left:19pt">Impairment and other charges (gains), net for the quarter and six months 2021 reflected $98 million and $233 million, respectively, primarily due to strategic gains related to the sale of McDonald&#8217;s Japan stock, which reduced the Company's total ownership by 3% for the quarter and 6% for the six months. As of June 30, 2021, the Company owned approximately 38% of McDonald's Japan. Results for the quarter and six months 2020 reflected the write-off of impaired software of $12 million and $26 million, respectively. The six months 2020 was partly offset by $13 million of income primarily comprised of a reversal of a reserve associated with the Company's sale of its business in the India Delhi 1pt"></td></tr></table></div><div><font style="color:#000000;font-family:'Times New Roman',sans-serif;font-size:10pt;font-weight:400;line-height:120%">n&#47;m Not meaningful</font></div><div style="margin-bottom:8pt;margin-top:4.5pt;padding-left:22.5pt;text-indent:-22.5pt"><font style="color:#000000;font-family:'Times New Roman',sans-serif;font-size:10pt;font-weight:400;line-height:120%">&#8226;</font><font style="color:#000000;font-family:'Times New Roman',sans-serif;font-size:10pt;font-weight:700;line-height:120%;padding-left:19pt">Operating Income&#58;</font><font style="color:#000000;font-family:'Times New Roman',sans-serif;font-size:10pt;font-style:italic;font-weight:700;line-height:120%"> </font><font style="color:#000000;font-family:'Times New Roman',sans-serif;font-size:10pt;font-weight:400;line-height:120%">Operating income increased to $2,691.1 million for the quarter and $4,972.4 million for the six months. Results included $98 million and $233 million for the quarter and six months, respectively, of net strategic gains primarily related to the sale of McDonald's Japan stock. </font></div><div style="margin-top:4.5pt;padding-left:45pt;text-indent:-22.5pt"><font style="color:#000000;font-family:'Times New Roman',sans-serif;font-size:10pt;font-style:italic;font-weight:700;line-height:120%">&#8226;</font><font style="color:#000000;font-family:'Times New Roman',sans-serif;font-size:10pt;font-weight:700;line-height:120%;padding-left:19pt">U.S.&#58;</font><font style="color:#000000;font-family:'Times New Roman',sans-serif;font-size:10pt;font-style:italic;font-weight:700;line-height:120%"> </font><font style="color:#000000;font-family:'Times New Roman',sans-serif;font-size:10pt;font-weight:400;line-height:120%">The operating income increase for the quarter and six months was driven by strong sales performance and higher gains on sales of restaurant businesses in the current year.</font></div><div style="margin-top:4.5pt;padding-left:45pt;text-indent:-22.5pt"><font style="color:#000000;font-family:'Times New Roman',sans-serif;font-size:10pt;font-weight:400;line-height:120%">&#8226;</font><font style="color:#000000;font-family:'Times New Roman',sans-serif;font-size:10pt;font-weight:700;line-height:120%;padding-left:19pt">International Operated Markets</font><font style="color:#000000;font-family:'Times New Roman',sans-serif;font-size:10pt;font-style:italic;font-weight:700;line-height:120%">&#58; </font><font style="color:#000000;font-family:'Times New Roman',sans-serif;font-size:10pt;font-weight:400;line-height:120%">The operating income increase for the quarter and six months was driven by strong sales performance, primarily in the U.K. and France.</font></div><div style="margin-top:4.5pt;padding-left:45pt;text-indent:-22.5pt"><font style="color:#000000;font-family:'Times New Roman',sans-serif;font-size:10pt;font-weight:400;line-height:120%">&#8226;</font><font style="color:#000000;font-family:'Times New Roman',sans-serif;font-size:10pt;font-weight:700;line-height:120%;padding-left:19pt">International Developmental Licensed Markets &#38; Corporate&#58;</font><font style="color:#000000;font-family:'Times New Roman',sans-serif;font-size:10pt;font-style:italic;font-weight:700;line-height:120%"> </font><font style="color:#000000;font-family:'Times New Roman',sans-serif;font-size:10pt;font-weight:400;line-height:120%">Excluding the strategic gains, results for the quarter and six months reflected strong sales performance driven by Japan and China and the benefit from comparisons to prior year reserves for bad debts, partly offset by higher Corporate general and administrative expenses due to increased incentive-based compensation in the current year.</font></div><div style="margin-top:8pt;padding-left:22.5pt;text-indent:-22.5pt"><font style="color:#000000;font-family:'Times New Roman',sans-serif;font-size:10pt;font-style:italic;font-weight:700;line-height:120%">&#8226;</font><font style="color:#000000;font-family:'Times New Roman',sans-serif;font-size:10pt;font-weight:700;line-height:120%;padding-left:19pt">Operating Margin&#58;</font><font style="color:#000000;font-family:'Times New Roman',sans-serif;font-size:10pt;font-weight:400;line-height:120%"> Operating margin is defined as operating income as a percent of total revenues. The contributions to operating margin differ by segment due to each segment's ownership structure, primarily due to the relative percentage of franchised versus Company-operated restaurants. Additionally, temporary restaurant closures, which vary by segment, impact the contribution of each segment to the consolidated operating margin. </font></div><div style="margin-top:4.5pt;padding-left:22.5pt"><font style="color:#000000;font-family:'Times New Roman',sans-serif;font-size:10pt;font-weight:400;line-height:120%">Excluding the strategic gains, the increase in operating margin percent for the quarter and six months was driven by stronger sales performance and higher other operating income.</font></div><div style="margin-top:4.5pt"><font><br></font></div><div id="i9f69d7e15d424fb0868db396c4337e5a_43"></div><div><font><br></font></div><div><font style="color:#000000;font-family:'Times New Roman',sans-serif;font-size:10pt;font-weight:700;line-height:120%">Interest Expense </font></div><div style="margin-top:4.5pt;padding-left:22.5pt;text-indent:-22.5pt"><font style="color:#000000;font-family:'Times New Roman',sans-serif;font-size:10pt;font-weight:400;line-height:120%">&#8226;</font><font style="color:#000000;font-family:'Times New Roman',sans-serif;font-size:10pt;font-weight:400;line-height:120%;padding-left:19pt">Interest expense decreased 7% (9% in constant currencies) for the quarter and was flat (decreased 2% in constant currencies) for the six months, primarily due to lower average debt balances partly offset by the impact of foreign currency translation and higher average interest rates.</font></div><div 0;text-align:right;vertical-align:bottom"></td></tr></table></div><div><font><br></font></div><div id="i9f69d7e15d424fb0868db396c4337e5a_49"></div><div><font><br></font></div><div><font style="color:#000000;font-family:'Times New Roman',sans-serif;font-size:10pt;font-weight:700;line-height:120%">Income Taxes</font></div><div style="margin-top:4.5pt;padding-left:22.5pt;text-indent:-22.5pt"><font style="color:#000000;font-family:'Times New Roman',sans-serif;font-size:10pt;font-weight:400;line-height:120%">&#8226;</font><font style="color:#000000;font-family:'Times New Roman',sans-serif;font-size:10pt;font-weight:400;line-height:120%;padding-left:19pt">The effective income tax rate was 6.6% and 25.4% for the quarters ended 2021 and 2020, respectively, and 13.2% and 24.0% for the six months ended 2021 and 2020, respectively. </font></div><div style="margin-top:4.5pt;padding-left:22.5pt;text-indent:-22.5pt"><font style="color:#000000;font-family:'Times New Roman',sans-serif;font-size:10pt;font-weight:400;line-height:120%">&#8226;</font><font style="color:#000000;font-family:'Times New Roman',sans-serif;font-size:10pt;font-weight:400;line-height:120%;padding-left:19pt">Excluding a benefit of $364 million related to deferred tax adjustments as a result of a change in the U.K. statutory income tax rate and the tax impact of the strategic gains, the non-GAAP effective income tax rate was 21.7% for the quarter and 21.3% for the six months.</font></div><div style="height:45pt;position:relative;width:100%"><div style="bottom:0;position:absolute;width:100%"><div style="text-align:center"><font style="color:#000000;font-family:'Times New Roman',sans-serif;font-size:10pt;font-weight:400;line-height:120%">9</font></div></div></div><div id="i9f69d7e15d424fb0868db396c4337e5a_55"></div><hr style="page-break-after:always"><div style="min-height:45pt;width:100%"><div><font><br></font></div></div><div style="margin-top:4.5pt"><font style="color:#000000;font-family:'Times New Roman',sans-serif;font-size:10pt;font-weight:700;line-height:120%">Outlook </font></div><div style="margin-top:4.5pt"><font style="color:#000000;font-family:'Times New Roman',sans-serif;font-size:10pt;font-weight:400;line-height:120%;text-decoration:underline">2021 Outlook</font></div><div style="margin-top:4.5pt;text-indent:22.5pt"><font style="color:#000000;font-family:'Times New Roman',sans-serif;font-size:10pt;font-weight:400;line-height:120%">Based on current conditions, the following is provided to assist in forecasting the Company's future results for 2021.</font></div><div style="margin-top:4.5pt;padding-left:22.5pt;text-indent:-22.5pt"><font style="color:#000000;font-family:'Times New Roman',sans-serif;font-size:10pt;font-weight:400;line-height:120%">&#8226;</font><font style="color:#000000;font-family:'Times New Roman',sans-serif;font-size:10pt;font-weight:400;line-height:120%;padding-left:19pt">The Company expects 2021 Systemwide sales growth, in constant currencies, in the mid-to-high teens, and expects net restaurant unit expansion to contribute about 1% to 2021 Systemwide sales growth. </font></div><div style="margin-top:4.5pt;padding-left:22.5pt;text-indent:-22.5pt"><font style="color:#000000;font-family:'Times New Roman',sans-serif;font-size:10pt;font-weight:400;line-height:120%">&#8226;</font><font style="color:#000000;font-family:'Times New Roman',sans-serif;font-size:10pt;font-weight:400;line-height:120%;padding-left:19pt">The Company expects operating margin percent to be in the low-to-mid 40% range.  </font></div><div style="margin-top:4.5pt;padding-left:22.5pt;text-indent:-22.5pt"><font style="color:#000000;font-family:'Times New Roman',sans-serif;font-size:10pt;font-weight:400;line-height:120%">&#8226;</font><font style="color:#000000;font-family:'Times New Roman',sans-serif;font-size:10pt;font-weight:400;line-height:120%;padding-left:19pt">The Company expects full year 2021 selling, general and administrative expenses of approximately 2.4% of Systemwide sales. </font></div><div style="margin-top:4.5pt;padding-left:22.5pt;text-indent:-22.5pt"><font style="color:#000000;font-family:'Times New Roman',sans-serif;font-size:10pt;font-weight:400;line-height:120%">&#8226;</font><font style="color:#000000;font-family:'Times New Roman',sans-serif;font-size:10pt;font-weight:400;line-height:120%;padding-left:19pt">Based on current interest and foreign currency exchange rates, the Company expects full year 2021 interest expense to decrease about 1% to 3% due primarily to lower average debt balances as the Company expects to reduce current debt levels to return to pre-COVID-19 leverage ratios.   </font></div><div style="margin-top:4.5pt;padding-left:22.5pt;text-indent:-22.5pt"><font style="color:#000000;font-family:'Times New Roman',sans-serif;font-size:10pt;font-weight:400;line-height:120%">&#8226;</font><font style="color:#000000;font-family:'Times New Roman',sans-serif;font-size:10pt;font-weight:400;line-height:120%;padding-left:19pt">The Company expects the effective income tax rate for the second half of 2021 to be in the 21% to 23% range. Some volatility may result in a quarterly tax rate outside of this range.</font></div><div style="margin-top:4.5pt;padding-left:22.5pt;text-indent:-22.5pt"><font style="color:#000000;font-family:'Times New Roman',sans-serif;font-size:10pt;font-weight:700;line-height:120%">&#8226;</font><font style="color:#000000;font-family:'Times New Roman',sans-serif;font-size:10pt;font-weight:400;line-height:120%;padding-left:19pt">The Company expects 2021 capital expenditures to be approximately $2.3 billion, about half of which will be directed towards new unit expansion across the U.S. and International Operated Markets. </font></div><div style="margin-top:4.5pt;padding-left:22.5pt"><font style="color:#000000;font-family:'Times New Roman',sans-serif;font-size:10pt;font-weight:400;line-height:120%">In 2021, about $1.1 billion will be dedicated to our U.S. business, about $550 million of which will be allocated to about 1,300 restaurant modernization projects. Globally, the Company expects to open over 1,300 restaurants. We will open over 450 restaurants in the U.S. and International Operated Markets segments, and our developmental licensee and affiliates will contribute capital towards over 850 restaurant openings in their respective markets. Additionally, the U.S. expects to close roughly 325 restaurants in 2021&#59; a majority of which are lower sales volume McDonald's in Walmart locations. The Company expects about 650 net restaurant additions in 2021.</font></div><div style="margin-top:4.5pt;padding-left:22.5pt;text-indent:-22.5pt"><font style="color:#000000;font-family:'Times New Roman',sans-serif;font-size:10pt;font-weight:400;line-height:112%">&#8226;</font><font style="color:#000000;font-family:'Times New Roman',sans-serif;font-size:10pt;font-weight:400;line-height:112%;padding-left:19pt">The Company expects to achieve a free cash flow conversion rate greater than 90%.</font></div><div
